para_trans: Appointment of "Inquiry Officer" in the case of Divisional Enquiry of Dr. Sachin Dilip Bari, then Sub-Divisional Police Officer, Daund Sub-Division, Pune Rural
GOVERNMENT ORDER NUMBER: ENQ-2020 / Q.No.73 / POL-2
Madame Cama Marg, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk, Mumbai-400 032
1) Government Memorandum, Home Department, No: ENQ-2020 / P.No.73 / Poll-2, dated 23/11/2020.
2) Government Circular, General Administration Department, No.: Nos. -1995 / Q. 2/95/10 -A, dated 18/05/1996.

While Dr. Secretary Dilip Bari, Sub-Divisional Police Officer, Daund Sub-Division, Pune Rural, is involved in the disciplinary case, a departmental inquiry is being conducted against him as per the procedure laid down in Rule 8 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Discipline and Appeal) Rules, 1979.
and, therefore, to inquire into the charges framed against them.
An inquiry officer should be appointed. The governor believes that

So now, Ma. The Governor, in exercise of the powers conferred by rule 8, proviso (2) to the said rules and in accordance with the relevant Government decision, is appointing the "Regional Divisional Investigation Officer, Pune Division, Pune" as the "Investigating Officer" to inquire into the charges framed against the aforesaid specified officer.
